<item>
            <title>[DERBY-229] Column names on ResultSet.updateXXX and getXXX methods are handled incorrectly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-229</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Sections 14.2.3 and &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;14.2.3&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; of JDBC 3.0 spec say&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Column names supplied to getter &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;updater&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; methods are case insensitive. If a select list&lt;br/&gt;
contains the same column more than once, the first instance of the column will be&lt;br/&gt;
returned &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;updated&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Derby returns or updates the last column in the select list, not the first. With the attached Java class I see&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;PRE-UPDATE&lt;br/&gt;
1,100&lt;br/&gt;
POST-UPDATE&lt;br/&gt;
1,500&lt;br/&gt;
POST-UPDATE getXXX(name)&lt;br/&gt;
AB:500,ab500&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
