                            <comment id="63123" author="djd" created="Tue, 19 Apr 2005 12:10:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also present in 10.0.2.1 for getXXX only (since updateXXX not supported)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="63128" author="mamtas" created="Tue, 19 Apr 2005 13:39:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The getter &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;updater&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; methods with column names (in EmbedResultSet.java) use the protected method findColumnName(String columnName) to determine the column index for the passed column name. And the loop for the lookup starts from the end towards the beginning of the ResultDescription and that seems to be the problem behind the current behavior. &lt;br/&gt;
	ResultDescription rd = resultDescription;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    	// 1 or 0 based? assume 1 (probably wrong)&lt;br/&gt;
    	for (int i=rd.getColumnCount(); i&amp;gt;=1; i--) {&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    		String name = rd.getColumnDescriptor&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/information.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;.getName();&lt;br/&gt;
    		if (StringUtil.SQLEqualsIgnoreCase(columnName, name)) &lt;/p&gt;
{
    			return i;
    		}
&lt;p&gt;    	}&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="66927" author="bandaram" created="Fri, 3 Jun 2005 06:33:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I believe I checked in fix for Shreyas for this bug. Shreyas, can you resolve and close this bug?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="66970" author="shreyas" created="Fri, 3 Jun 2005 14:56:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patched has been submitted which was committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="66971" author="shreyas" created="Fri, 3 Jun 2005 14:57:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing this issue as it was patched&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
